      <p><em>— Ahmad Zaki, Fleet Manager</em></p>

      <h2>Planning Your Maintenance Reserve</h2>

      <h3>Step 1: Calculate Expected Maintenance Costs</h3>

      <p>For each prime mover:
      <br>• Based on age, brand, mileage
      <br>• Include routine maintenance
      <br>• Add major repair projections
      <br>• Include 20-30% buffer</p>

      <h3>Step 2: Determine Reserve Size</h3>

      <p>Calculate:
      <br>• Total annual maintenance budget
      <br>• Desired months of coverage (6-12 months recommended)
      <br>• Reserve target: Annual budget × coverage months</p>

      <h3>Step 3: Bundle in Financing</h3>

      <p>Work with financier to:
      <br>• Add maintenance reserve to loan amount
      <br>• Structure payments to rebuild reserve after drawdowns
      <br>• Ensure reserve can be accessed easily when repairs needed</p>

      <h3>Step 4: Track and Replenish</h3>

      <p>Maintain:
      <br>• Reserve balance tracking
      <br>• Monthly reconciliation
      <br>• Withdrawal documentation
      <br>• Reserve replenishment schedule</p>

